translated: Looram, Max Albert Maria Lison, practicing physician, Gothenburg, b. 8/7/87 in Dresden to merchant Oskar Ferdinand Larsson and Theodolinda Ulrica Katarina Janzon. Married on 23 with pharmacist Thyra Johanna Fredrika Berggren. Children: Kerstin Margareta b. 26. — Obtained M.A. in Lund in 1907, M.Sc. in Medicine in 1912, and Medical License in 1923 in Stockholm. Worked as a physician in several districts from 1919-1923, assistant physician at St. Eriks Hospital from 1923-1924, acting district physician in Gothenburg from 1925, and practicing physician there since 1924. Field medical grant in 1914, battalion physician in reserve from 1923-1924, reinstated in 1940.
